      • compare2CSVFiles

        public static CSVData compare2CSVFiles(CSVData olderCSVData,
                       CSVData youngerCSVData)
        This method will initialize the columns which are used as identifiers in the comparison. Then it will decide based on the given command line arguments how the files will be compared.
        Parameters:
        olderCSVData - the object with the CSVData which should be considered as older in the comparison
        youngerCSVData - the object with the CSVData which should be considered as younger in the comparison

      • doComparisionWithHierarchy

        private static CSVData doComparisionWithHierarchy(CSVData olderCSVData,
                                 CSVData youngerCSVData,
                                 Column identifierColumnOlder,
                                 Column identifierColumnYounger)
        !!!!!!!!!!!!!! UNDER CONSTRUCTION !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

        This method is used when the arguments "-hierarchy" and "-hierarchyColumn" is provided. It will split the provided CSVData in parts, with the topLevel as a "delimiter". This method considers also hierarchical relations between the rows in the data, and creates subsets of CSVData in the parts. The parts are compared if in both files a topLevel with the same identifier is found. The result of all part comparisons is merged in one result file.

        Parameters:
        olderCSVData - the object with the CSVData which should be considered as older in the comparison
        youngerCSVData - the object with the CSVData which should be considered as younger in the comparison
        identifierColumnOlder - the column of the older CSVData which is used to identify the record
        identifierColumnYounger - the column of the older CSVData which is used to identify the record

      • doComparisionWithTopLevel

        private static CSVData doComparisionWithTopLevel(CSVData olderCSVData,
                                CSVData youngerCSVData,
                                Column identifierColumnOlder,
                                Column identifierColumnYounger)
        This method is used when the argument "-column.toplevel" is provided. It will split the provided CSVData in parts, with the topLevel as a "delimiter". The parts are compared if in both files a topLevel with the same identifier is found. The result of all part comparisons is merged in one result file.
        Parameters:
        olderCSVData - the object with the CSVData which should be considered as older in the comparison
        youngerCSVData - the object with the CSVData which should be considered as younger in the comparison
        identifierColumnOlder - the column of the older CSVData which is used to identify the record
        identifierColumnYounger - the column of the older CSVData which is used to identify the record

      • doDefaultComparision

        private static CSVData doDefaultComparision(CSVData olderCSVData,
                           CSVData youngerCSVData,
                           Column identifierColumnOlder,
                           Column identifierColumnYounger)
        This method is used when no "-column.compareDef" arguments are provided. It will compare all columns which has the same header in both files.

        youngerCSVData - the object with the CSVData which should be considered as younger in the comparison
        identifierColumnOlder - the column of the older CSVData which is used to identify the record
        identifierColumnYounger - the column of the older CSVData which is used to identify the record
